Fix CharBox crash on zero-length (empty) strings.

`if ($str)` is falsy for an empty string '', so CharBox left an uninitialized
pointer with len 0. The text path then passed that uninitialized pointer to
libsql_text() (segfault) and the blob path computed `len - 1` = -1 = SIZE_MAX
(Rust capacity-overflow abort). Inserting '' into any column killed the PHP
process. Allocating for any non-null string (including '') fixes both paths.

Upstream: https://github.com/tursodatabase/turso-php  (report me)
--- a/src/CharBox.php
+++ b/src/CharBox.php
@@ -19,7 +19,7 @@
         $cStr = $ffi->new("char *");
         $cLen = 0;

-        if ($str) {
+        if ($str !== null) {
             $cLen = strlen($str) + 1;
             $cStr = $ffi->new($ffi::arrayType($ffi->type("char"), [$cLen]), owned: false);
             $ffi::memcpy($cStr, $str, strlen($str));
